  "abstract": "Labile carbon pools, comprising rapidly and moderately degradable fractions of soil organic carbon, are key indicators of soil quality and carbon dynamics, extracted through sequential acid hydrolysis to assess short- and long-term nutrient cycling. Assessing these pools offers valuable insights into carbon dynamics, soil quality, and resilience in agricultural systems.",
